718461f-a.folder: Central Park West & 71st Street, Manhattan, NY
718461f-a.text:
Central Park West, west side, from 71st to 74th Streets. In the centre may be seen the erection of the Majestic Apartment House, rising on the site of the old Majestic Hotel. Immediately beyond it, from 72nd to 73rd Streets, is the Dakota, one of the oldest apartment houses in the city. The two apartment houses beyond the Dakota are the Langham and the San Remo. January 8, 1931.

P. L. Sparr, Photographer.
718461f-a.title: Manhattan: Central Park West - 71st Street

718462f-a.folder: Central Park West & 71st Street, Manhattan, NY
718462f-a.text:
The Majestic Apartment House, Central Park West, west side, from 71st to 72nd Streets, from Central Park. This building replaces the Majestic Hotel.
1932.
THE NEW YORK
PUBLIC LIBRARY

718464f-a.folder: Central Park West & 71st Street (West), Manhattan, NY
718464f-a.text:
Central Park West, north from West 71st Street and showing apartment buildings facing Central Park. The Hotel Majestic is in the center, occupying the entire block front from 71st to 72nd Streets. On the left are the Lorington and the Barnard respectively.
September 1914.
George L. Balgue.
